WorkItem.Description:
I'm having trouble adding a css rule with escaping in a LESS file, as described here: http://lesscss.org/#-escaping.

If i add the example rule from the link:

filter: ~"progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.AlphaImageLoader(src='image.png')";

I get the following error:

Error	201	Expected '}' on line 34 in file 'include/css3.less':
 [33]: 	background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear, left top, left bottom, from(@from), to(@to));
 [34]: 	filter: ~"progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.AlphaImageLoader(src='image.png')";
       -^

Does the LESS parser included in Chirpy support LESS escaping ?
